      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is just preserving the existing behavior. If the string.isEmpty() the don\u0027t write anything at all, not even the id (so Deserialize will never see any of this and just leave the respective string empty). Note that all of these \u0027write\u0027s and \u0027read\u0027s are asymmetric in that the \u0027write\u0027s write out the id, but the \u0027read\u0027s don\u0027t read in the id since the id must already be read in order to decide which \u0027read\u0027 to call. The \u0027read\u0027 is written defensively, I suppose it doesn\u0027t really need to be.",
      "parentUuid": "eec60ac7_72dcea0c",
