      "writtenOn": "2018-05-17T15:38:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmmm... I don\u0027t think this write32 invalidates old pictures, but the change above to readS32 for this data does. I\u0027ll have to do the picture version dance here because this is actually a bug fix. The axes are allowed to be negative, and writePackedUInt / readPackedUInt will mess that up.\n\nI will also note that writePackedUInt takes a size_t, but won\u0027t write more than 32 bits and readPackedUInt claims to read a size_t but can only read up to uint32_t. But this is a different existing issue which I hope this change makes easier to fix.",
